==English==
===Idiom===
'''[[Rock]] [[Paper]] [[Scissors]]'''
# a popular child's game played by using hand signs. Two players face each other with one hand out flat - palm facing up, other hand in a fist strikes the palm three times weilding one of three hand symbols. Remaining a fist for "rock", 'peace' sign pointed at opponent for "scissors", hand out flat with palm facing down for "paper". Rock beats scissors; scissors beat paper; paper beats rock. Loser often requests "best two out of three".
